      "writtenOn": "2020-06-09T13:17:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the best practice for something like this is to have a helper package with zero dependencies (maybe even tests to ensure that no dependencies get added) designed specifically for this purpose. Task scheduler kind of does that with the poorly named \"specs\" package which is imported by gen_tasks in the client repos, but it could be more minimal. Seems useful for Gold too, maybe depending on how much of it is handled by goldctl.",
