      "writtenOn": "2020-06-09T12:04:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m somewhat surprised that we don\u0027t have a built-in for this.  We may not need to worry about it for this use case, but floating point arithmetic can be surprisingly subtle, especially when len(d) is large, or values in d are large or widely varying.  If you think it might be a concern, some easy tricks would be to sort d into ascending order before summing, or just use a double for the accumulator.  This would also apply above.",
